1+\tan{x}=\frac{\sin{(\frac{\pi}{4}+x)}}{\cos{\frac{\pi}{4}}\cos{x}}=\sqrt{2}\frac{\cos{(\frac{\pi}{4}-x)}}{\cos{x}}
\cos \frac {\pi}{4}=\sin \frac {\pi}{4}=\frac1{\sqrt2}
1+\tan x=1+\frac{\sin x}{\cos x}=\frac{\cos x+\sin x}{\cos x}\frac{\frac1{\sqrt2}}{\frac1{\sqrt2}}=\frac{\cos x\sin \frac {\pi}{4}+\sin x\cos \frac {\pi}{4}}{\cos \frac{\pi}{4}\cos x}=\frac{\sin\left(x+\frac{\pi}{4}\right)}{\cos \frac{\pi}{4}\cos x}
